---
import Legal from '../layouts/Legal.astro';
---

<Legal
  title="Refund Policy — TradingView Optimizer"
  description="All subscription sales are final. Cancel anytime to stop future renewals."
  heading="Refund Policy"
  updated="April 17, 2026"
>

<div class="callout callout-warn">
  <p>
    <strong>All sales are final.</strong> We do not offer refunds or
    credits for subscription payments, including unused time on a monthly
    or annual plan. You can cancel your subscription at any time to stop
    future renewals.
  </p>
</div>

<h2>1. Why we don't issue refunds</h2>

<p>
  We offer a free trial before any charge so you can evaluate every
  feature of TradingView Optimizer without commitment. Because you have
  the opportunity to test the product in full before subscribing, we
  operate a strict no-refund policy once a paid subscription begins.
</p>

<h2>2. How cancellation works</h2>

<ul>
  <li>
    You can cancel at any time from your
    <a href="/dashboard">dashboard</a> or through the Stripe billing
    portal.
  </li>
  <li>
    When you cancel, your subscription remains active through the end of
    the billing period you have already paid for. You keep full access
    until that date.
  </li>
  <li>
    After that date, your subscription will not renew, and you will not
    be charged again.
  </li>
  <li>
    We do not pro-rate or refund the unused portion of any billing
    period, whether monthly or annual.
  </li>
</ul>

<h2>3. Annual plans</h2>

<p>
  Annual plans are billed once per year in full at the start of the
  billing period. If you cancel partway through an annual period, you
  keep access until the end of that year, but we do not refund any
  portion of the annual charge.
</p>

<h2>4. Failed or disputed payments</h2>

<p>
  If a renewal payment fails, Stripe may automatically retry the charge
  in accordance with its standard retry schedule. We may suspend or
  terminate your access until payment is brought current. Initiating a
  chargeback instead of contacting us first may result in immediate
  termination of your account.
</p>

<h2>5. Exceptional circumstances</h2>

<p>
  In rare cases — for example, a duplicate charge caused by a billing
  error, or an unauthorized charge caused by compromised account
  credentials — we may issue a refund at our sole discretion. If you
  believe one of these situations applies to you, contact us within
  <strong>14 days</strong> of the charge at
  <a href="mailto:legal@tradingviewoptimizer.com">legal@tradingviewoptimizer.com</a>
  with the date of the charge and a brief description of the issue.
</p>

<h2>6. Taxes</h2>

<p>
  Any applicable taxes collected at checkout are remitted to the
  appropriate authority and are not refundable from us. If you believe
  tax was charged in error, contact us and we will work with Stripe to
  review the charge.
</p>

<h2>7. Changes to this policy</h2>

<p>
  We may update this Refund Policy from time to time. Any change applies
  only to subscriptions purchased on or after the "Last updated" date at
  the top of this page.
</p>

<h2>8. Contact</h2>

<p>
  Billing questions:
  <a href="mailto:legal@tradingviewoptimizer.com">legal@tradingviewoptimizer.com</a>.
  See also our <a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a> for the full
  subscription terms.
</p>

</Legal>
